===Noun===
{{wikipedia|Harrow (tool)}}
{{en-noun}}

#(farm implement) A device, pulled by a tractor, with several disks or teeth in a row to smooth or break up soil, typically after plowing, or to remove weeds or cover seeds; a harrow [[plow]].



===Verb===
'''harrow'''

#To subject to a [[harrowing]] experience; to [[traumatize]]; to frighten or torment.
#:''The headless horseman '''harrow'''ed Ichabod Crane as he tried to reach the bridge.''
#(Christian theology) The freeing of the souls of the dead from Sheol (Hades, traditionally called hell) by Christ between his death and resurrection.

